translated: DO NOT ORDER ONLINE! STAY AWAY! On Mother's Day I placed a large order online costing almost $80 at 5:19pm. Pick up time was 5:59. I arrived at the restaurant at 5:58 and called in for curb side pickup. I was told I could wait 10 minutes while they boiled pasta (thats right boil pasta) for one of my meals or I could order something that they could make faster. It takes 9 (NINE) minutes to cook noddles, if they need 10 minutes that means they have NOT started making the meal yet. While I waited I call back to speak to the manager who said a few things that really stuck out; "....ordering online does NOT reflect what we have in store." Also that they had used "my" pasta for another order. He did NOT offer anything for the inconvenience and would NOT cancel my order after I made multiple requests for him to do so. When the order came out I made the sever go back inside and get her manager. She came back with two men. One was the manager I had spoke with, the other had tattoos covering both arms said nothing and stood over me the whole time (don't complain the might beat you up lol). What a JOKE!(yes I mean him and the store) There were also two other employees sitting outside in front of my car watching the show! I opened all the orders only handling mine and my wife. My CF steak was cold and soggy. I made him give money back for the CF steak and the pasta which was the problem in the first place. When I finally returned home with the food my family was sorely disappointed with the quality and temperature of their meals. Most of the food was discard to the garage(where it belonged). WASTE OF TIME and MONEY! Not so much rude as flat out incompetent! BOB EVENS had NO intention of having my order completed on time, even tho they able to do so.

translated: Was here for the first time today and I really liked it as soon as I walked in. It's not run-of-the-mill furniture, but rather reminiscent of burger shops in the USA. The only thing is that it is very narrow. Ordering the food was very uncomplicated and I was able to order to my heart's content: BBQ Bacon Cheese Burger, small. Fries and Fritz-Cola for €12.70. Waiting time approx. 10 minutes (lunchtime). Bite into it, no excessive messing around (like in so many other burger shops), fries with potato skins, 2 sauces of your choice (Currymayo and Heinz Ketchup), Cola of course went perfectly with it. In terms of taste, the burger was right up there, great BBQ sauce on it, meat perfectly medium, juicy bacon, fresh salad, etc. Fries well salted, mayo sauce slightly oily. Conclusion: Successful lunch, it's worth coming back.

They are so nice.  They will make your food to your specifications. The service is great!  And most of all, the best food around!  My favorite dishes are the spicy tuna roll (he makes his own spicy sauce made from hot peppers and other spices...it is soo hot, but I cannot have sushi without it!) The teriyaki chicken is phenomenal, the beef tetaki is also fantastic...The vegetables are always fresh, the meat is always tender and seasoned to perfection, they always give you the best fruit after your meal...sometimes complimentary.  I honestly cannot say enough about this place.  It may not look very inviting from the outside, but I promise...you will have a great dining experience here.  I have turned so many people into Akashi fans and sushi lovers by taking them here.  I have been coming here for 6 years or more and will continue to be a proud patron.

The highlight of our meal though was "cài with 3 chillies" - a vegetarian(!) main our waiter recommended - triple fried tofu that was just out of this world.  Eating at Kai is likely to dent your wallet quite a bit - but it's well worth it. Very upmarket, very sophisticated and well deserving of it's Michelin star. I mean, if frozen shoe string fries from the frozen section of your local Associated is your thing, then, by all means, go ahead, but I don't have to live like some animal.

After we received the card quite quickly, it took about 20 minutes until we could place our order. Changes to the order only come with a hefty surcharge. Not all products listed on the menu were also available. We ordered food and drinks together. The drinks came after 15 minutes. We both ordered a Fanta, and it was served without consultation by the waiter Merinda. After us came a soccer team and another 5 minutes later another couple. The footballers ordered and received their food after 10 minutes. The couple after 15 minutes. The football players had already finished eating and we still didn't have our food. 35 minutes after placing our order we left the restaurant without eating and without paying.

So we were worried that as it was their first night there will be problems.  The service at the start was slow but the manageress was so lovely, she apologised for the previous owners and really made the whole family feel comfortable.  The food was really nice, especially the lamb & mousakka.  There was traditional greek music whilst we were eating and after the manageress got us all up doing some greek dancing late into the night, then a disco.  All in all we had a fantastic night and I will definately be coming back soon.

Unbelievable! The whole thing was very amateurish it was hard to believe it had been running for a year. Was going to visit with friends but will go to Jimmy's farm instead...not cheap there but much better value....such a pity as the setting is wonderful and we like a place where you can see into the kitchen.

translated: I love Tara Thai! My husband and I probably go to Tara about once a week, on average.  They have the best Happy Hour in the area, and they are awesome at making drinks.  The food is absolutely delicious!  I can't rave enough about the: Green Curry, Panang, Pattaya noodles, sea food madness, tom klong gong soup, and many more!   If you're there for happy hour, get the calamari!  The quality of the squid is top-notch, and the unique sauce is great!  The customer service is phenomenal, especially for regulars.  Everyone truly cares and wants the customer to have a good experience, and the manager is great.   My only minor complaint is that, personally, I like my thai food to be a little bit spicier than how they make it (but I'm a head-addict when it comes to food).. but I just ask for the spice tray and add more spice.. works perfectly!  Can't stress enough how yummy and enjoyable this place is!  My advice: Make this your "cheers bar" and eat up!

name: Thai Tom
translated: I walked into the Chowder Pot for the first time on a Friday evening and was not even greeted with a hello, how many, or how can I help you from the hostesses.  I had to make the initial conversation at the hostess desk.  I was trying to ask a few questions about sitting at the bar and my responses were given to me in a short, nasty tone with absolutely no smile.  I felt as if I was bothering her and she did not want to help me.  The first 3 minutes at the Chowder Pot made me want to leave immediately.  Thankfully I had an amazingly wonderful waitress who made up for the hostess lack of friendly personality. The food was mediocre but delivered in a timely fashion.  I decided to stay in the bar/lounge area after dinner where yet again the servers were wonderful, friendly, had personality, and smiled (unlike the hostess).  Unfortunately my debit card was wrongfully charged and when I called Saturday morning to solve the problem the response I received was not very helpful, not apologetic, and yet again I felt as if I was bothering them as if it was my fault the mistake was made.  The people who actually work at Chowder Pot made the experience a great one, the hostess however needs to further her education in How to Have a Happy Personality and Smile as she is in the hospitality/customer service business.  I will not be returning to Chowder Pot.
